com.vmware.appliance.vcenter.settings.v1.config.components.inventory.cluster.drs

Class DependencyRule

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.vmware.appliance.vcenter.settings.v1.config.components.inventory.cluster.drs.DependencyRule
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    com.vmware.vapi.bindings.StaticStructure, com.vmware.vapi.bindings.Structure, java.io.Serializable

    public final class DependencyRule
extends java.lang.Object
implements java.io.Serializable, com.vmware.vapi.bindings.StaticStructure
    The DependencyRule class defines VM-to-VM dependencies.

    A VM-VM Dependency rule identifies the following groups.

    • A virtual machine group - getVmGroup()
    • A "depends on" virtual machine group - getDependsOnVmGroup().

    The VMs in getVmGroup() depends on the list of VMs specified in getDependsOnVmGroup().
